definition[0]: if someone comes over, they visit you at your house
example[0]: Do you want to come over on Friday evening?
definition[1]: if someone comes over, they come to the country where you are
example[1]: When did your family first come over to America?
definition[2]: if a strong feeling comes over you, you suddenly experience it
example[2]: A wave of sleepiness came over me.
example[3]: I’m sorry about that – I don’t know what came over me  (=I do not know why I behaved in that way).
definition[3]: if an idea comes over well, people can understand it easily
example[4]: I thought that the points he was making came over quite clearly.
definition[4]: if someone comes over in a particular way, they seem to have particular qualities
example[5]: He didn’t come over very well (=seem to have good qualities)  in the interview.
example[6]: She comes over as a very efficient businesswoman.
definition[5]: to suddenly become very shy, nervous etc
